parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

fails to shift properly

makes loud noises
or causes vibrations while driving.

causing the wheel to fall off or seize

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck or inoperable, making it difficult or impossible to wear the seat belt, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor is stuck
the seat belt cannot be pulled out
the seat belt is loose
the seat belt tightens around the driver
the seat belt becomes stuck in the retractor
the seat belt does not retract or release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchor can cause the seat belt to become detached or unsecured, making it difficult or impossible to wear the seat belt, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt anchor becomes unattached
the seat belt disconnects from the floor anchor
the seat belt becomes misaligned
the seat belt buckle frequently releases from anchorage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latching mechanism can cause the seat belt to become stuck or inoperable, making it difficult or impossible to wear the seat belt, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch
the seat belt becomes stuck in the retractor
the seat belt does not retract or release
the seat belt tightens around the driver.
